{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EHOAC_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EHOAC_1}In the early 1840\u8217\'92s, Nicholas Farwell brought a lawsuit against his employer, the Boston & Worcester Rail Road.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F1539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F1539209744_ID0EPOAC_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F1539209744_ID0EPOAC_1}1}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 Farwell was an \u8220\'93engine-man\u8221\'94 who earned two dollars a day. One day in 1837, he suffered an accident, was thrown to the ground, and the wheels of a railroad car passed over his right hand and crushed it.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F2539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F2539209744_ID0EXOAC_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F2539209744_ID0EXOAC_1}2}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 The accident was caused (or so Farwell alleged) by the carelessness of other employees.}
