{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EAPAC_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EAPAC_1}The highest court of Massachusetts turned down Farwell\u8217\'92s claim. The Chief Justice of Massachusetts, Lemuel Shaw, wrote the opinion. Shaw was an important figure in the legal world of the nineteenth century; he would probably be surprised to learn that his fame today, such as it is, is mostly due to the fact that his son-in-law was the author Herman Melville. Shaw was a very able judge, however, and the }{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
Farwell}{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 case was one of his most notable and significant decisions.}
