{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E5PAC_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E5PAC_1}In any event, Nicholas Farwell\u8217\'92s lawsuit failed; and he was left without any money from the railroad. His life, even before the accident, was surely very different from the comfortable life of the Chief Justice of Massachusetts. I have no idea what Farwell\u8217\'92s life was like, after he lost his case. Did he have a wife and children? How did the family manage, after the accident? The crushed hand probably made it hard for him to earn a living. Today, every legal historian knows the case and recognizes Farwell\u8217\'92s name. But at the time, this kind of recognition would have been cold comfort to Farwell and his family.}
