{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EHEAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EHEAE_1}In any event, the fellow-servant rule, as Shaw formulated it, proved persuasive to other courts. Under American law, the states are legally sovereign, at least in matters of ordinary tort and contract law. No court was obliged to follow }{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
Farwell;}{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 it was Massachusetts law and had no force outside of the state\u8217\'92s borders. Yet almost every American court did adopt the fellow-servant rule.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F8539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F8539209744_ID0EGFAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F8539209744_ID0EGFAE_1}8}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 }{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
Farwell}{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
, then was not an idiosyncratic, one-off decision. It was a doctrinal move that other judges found convincing. To be sure, }{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
Farwell}{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 was a well-written, closely reasoned case by a leading and highly respected judge. No doubt this made some difference. But the fellow-servant rule would probably have made its way, even without the }{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
Farwell}{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 case, even without Shaw\u8217\'92s well-crafted opinion.}
