{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EULAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EULAE_1}The fellow-servant rule, of course, was not confined to railroads. And it became more and more important as industry grew in importance and in scale. The number of work accidents multiplied. In many instances, the fellow-servant rule blocked any chance the victim had to win damages. If there was negligence at all behind a work accident, it was likely to be the negligence of a fellow worker. At first, the courts stuck to the rule--a rule which they had, after all, invented. In time, however, the situation began to change. The sheer volume of accidents began to make a difference.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F14539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F14539209744_ID0ERMAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F14539209744_ID0ERMAE_1}14}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 Some judges, it seems clear, found the rule distasteful. Plaintiffs (or their lawyers) began to explore ways to avoid or modify the rule; they searched for holes or weaknesses in the doctrinal fabric. The rule itself was, in theory, fairly clear-cut. But it began to erode under the pressure of litigation. Not many lawsuits were successful; and there was an \u8220\'93enormous disproportion\u8221\'94 between the number of lawsuits, win or lose, and the thousands and thousands of \u8220\'93work-related injuries and deaths\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F15539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F15539209744_ID0EFNAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F15539209744_ID0EFNAE_1}15}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 But signs of decay became gradually obvious. The \u8220\'93architecture of the classical law of torts,\u8221\'94 including the fellow-servant rule, began to lose \u8220\'93its coherence and form\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F16539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F16539209744_ID0EUNAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F16539209744_ID0EUNAE_1}16}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 The rule sprouted a whole host of exceptions; and exceptions to exceptions.}
