{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E4NAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E4NAE_1}In a New Jersey case decided in 1865, a railroad bridge gave way when a \u8220\'93heavily loaded\u8221\'94 train of cars went over the bridge, and a brake-man, Philip Harrison, was killed.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F17539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F17539209744_ID0EFOAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F17539209744_ID0EFOAE_1}17}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 The administrator of his estate claimed that the railroad company was \u8220\'93aware\u8221\'94 that the bridge was \u8220\'93out of repair and was unsafe\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F18539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F18539209744_ID0EROAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F18539209744_ID0EROAE_1}18}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 The railroad demurred, no doubt on the basis of the fellow-servant rule. But the high court of New Jersey overruled the demurrer. The case paid lip-service to the fellow-servant rule, said it was \u8220\'93completely established,\u8221\'94 cited }{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
Farwell}{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
, but then went on to say that the rule did not apply to the negligence of the \u8220\'93master,\u8221\'94 rather than the negligence of a fellow-employee; the poor condition of the bridge was, presumably, the fault of the company as a whole, and therefore of the \u8220\'93master,\u8221\'94 and not one of his agents.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F19539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F19539209744_ID0EFPAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F19539209744_ID0EFPAE_1}19}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 Out of cases like this, there developed the so-called \u8220\'93vice-principal\u8221\'94 rule; the fellow-servant rule does not apply if the negligence comes from someone in authority in the company, a \u8220\'93person who so far represents the principal that the law charges the principal with liability for the acts ... of such person\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F20539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F20539209744_ID0EUPAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F20539209744_ID0EUPAE_1}20}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 In one case, for example, decided by the United States Supreme Court in 1884, the injured workman was an engineer, whose injury was caused by the \u8220\'93gross negligence\u8221\'94 of the conductor of the train.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F21539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F21539209744_ID0EZPAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F21539209744_ID0EZPAE_1}21}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 The conductor, who was in charge, was (in the Court\u8217\'92s view) \u8220\'93the personal representative of the corporation,\u8221\'94 and was therefore not really a fellow-servant at all.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F22539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F22539209744_ID0EHQAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F22539209744_ID0EHQAE_1}22}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 This doctrine blew a fairly big hole in the fellow-servant rule. So did a related rule which required the master to provide a \u8220\'93reasonably safe place to work in, and reasonably safe appliances with which to do the work\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F23539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
