{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EBTAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EBTAE_1}In the early twentieth century, in other words, there was increasing pressure on the fellow-servant rule. It became hard to ignore the appalling harvest of industrial accidents. In 1910, Crystal Eastman, supported by the Russell Sage Foundation, published a study of work accidents in Pittsburgh, part of a general \u8220\'93Pittsburgh survey\u8221\'94 in six volumes.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F29539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F29539209744_ID0EPTAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F29539209744_ID0EPTAE_1}29}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 Eastman in her book, made more vivid with stark photographs of workers and work conditions, laid out clearly and in detail the horrendous nature of work accidents, the crushing impact of these accidents on workers and their families, and the pitiful amounts that workers themselves and their widows and children were generally able to collect. Out of a group of 120 instances in which a married worker was killed, a quarter of the families got nothing at all; and more than half got $100 or less.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F30539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F30539209744_ID0E3TAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F30539209744_ID0E3TAE_1}30}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 Some employers were beginning to realize the \u8220\'93injustice of leaving the whole burden of accidents upon the workmen,\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F31539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F31539209744_ID0EIUAE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F31539209744_ID0EIUAE_1}31}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 and were providing some relief to the injured and their families. But other employers did nothing.}
