{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0EM3AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0EM3AE_1}Workers\u8217\'92 compensation blasted a huge hole in the traditional tort system. The appalling toll of accidental deaths was perhaps the crucial political factor. Also, the fellow-servant rule had become unwieldy as well as socially unsatisfying. John Witt has also connected the compensation movement with the dramatic rise of statistical knowledge.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F48539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F48539209744_ID0E43AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F48539209744_ID0E43AE_1}48}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 To Chief Justice Lemuel Shaw, as we saw, an \u8220\'93accident\u8221\'94 was a kind of random and unpredictable event; like being struck by lightning. In his day, no one was counting and measuring accidents. But by the late nineteenth century, it was possible to think of industrial accidents \u8220\'93in terms of probabilities\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F49539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F49539209744_ID0EG4AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F49539209744_ID0EG4AE_1}49}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 In many kinds of business--railroading, mining, construction--accidents were bound to happen. The same was true for all major projects. If a company had a contract to build a big bridge, or a skyscraper, or if a company planned to open a new coal mine, the company could reckon on a certain number of accidents, a certain number of injuries and deaths. There was no way to predict }{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
which}{\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 workers would die or be injured. But you could gage, more or less, how many deaths and injuries were bound to happen. Injuries on the job, then, became in a way \u8220\'93nobody\u8217\'92s fault in the personal sense\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F50539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F50539209744_ID0EI5AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F50539209744_ID0EI5AE_1}50}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 Each particular injury might be the result of a pure accident. But in the aggregate, deaths and injuries were an inevitable part of ordinary business; they were \u8220\'93attributable to the inherent hazards of industry\u8221\'94}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F51539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
