{\*\bkmkstart co_g_ID0E65AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_g_ID0E65AE_1}John Witt\u8217\'92s insight helps explain the rise of workers\u8217\'92 compensation. It connects the compensation movement to the rise of what has been called the metric society}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F52539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F52539209744_ID0EI6AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F52539209744_ID0EI6AE_1}52}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 Data, figures, and statistics made the dimensions of the problem clear; and cast the problem in a distinct new light. For many kinds of business--coal mines, railroads, and construction companies, for example-- accidents were inevitable, but measurable; they could therefore be anticipated, and thus at least potentially controlled and contained}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F53539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F53539209744_ID0EO6AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F53539209744_ID0EO6AE_1}53}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 The big change was not only in techniques of measurement, but also (and perhaps more profoundly) in the culture of risk. This was becoming, more and more, an insuring and insurable society. The insurance business grew enormously in the latter part of the nineteenth century}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F54539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_F54539209744_ID0EX6AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_F54539209744_ID0EX6AE_1}54}{}}}\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\fs20\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
 It is profitable precisely because of its ability to predict and measure risk.}
