 These phrases fit worker\u8217\'92s compensation as well; and (very notably) the American health system (or lack of one). There is no universal, national scheme of free health care, as we said. But there is Medicare for old people and Medicaid for poor people. There is \u8220\'93Obamacare\u8221\'94 There are health \u8220\'93benefits\u8221\'94 through the job, for millions of workers. Veterans are entitled to medical care at VA institutions. Congressmen have free medical care. There are special provisions for kidney dialysis, under a law passed by Congress in 1972.}{{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_F119539209744_1" }{\fldrslt {\hich\af5\loch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\strike0\super\f5\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\cf19\strike0\super\fs16\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\f5\loch
